INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(169, 1, '2011-05-24 21:29:31', '2011-05-24 21:29:31', '<h1>our responsibility</h1>\nWater is natural. Bottled water isn’t. But natural water can be tainted.\n\nIn the third world, contaminated water is one of the biggest factors in infant mortality. A child dies\nevery 30 seconds as a result. Even in the U.S., major cities have water supplies that contain lead,\nchemicals and other impurities.\n\nBetween Hawaii and California lies a toxic island twice the size of Texas, made from discarded,\ndisposable plastic bottles. Americans discard 60 million plastic bottles each day. Bottled water also\nharms the Earth. It wastes fossil fuels and water in production and transport. Not to mention, bottles\nbecome a major source of waste.\n\nWhat, then, is the solution? Bottled water?\n\nFact is, both regulation and enforcement of bottled water safety is weaker than that of tap water.\nFederal, state, and local environmental agencies require rigorous testing of tap water safety. For that\nreason, tap water is the very foundation of Apiqe water.\n\nFEWER BOTTLES , LESS WASTE\n\n•  According to the US Recycling Institute, more than 80% of bottles in the U.S. do not get recycled\nand end up in landfills\n\n•  By eliminating the transport of bottled water from manufacturers to distributors to\nrestaurants, offices and homes, pollution and energy consumption are greatly reduced\n\n•  Apiqe has the lightest carbon footprint in the industry', 'My World', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-autosave', '', '', '2011-05-24 21:29:31', '2011-05-24 21:29:31', '', 40, 'http://apiqe.com/2011/05/23/40-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
