INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(230, 1, '2011-05-25 14:23:58', '2011-05-25 14:23:58', '<h1>revolutionary technology</h1>\r\n<img src="http://apiqe.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/doted-lines-short.png"/>\r\n\r\nFew industry breakthroughs have ever made such a big splash. Apiqe redefines standards in water \r\npurification and filtration. In fact the actual experience of drinking water will never be the same!\r\n\r\nApiqe works simply. More simply than others. Others may filter and cleanse water directly at the supply. \r\nBut they’re bulky, multi-part and expensive. Unlike Apiqe.\r\n\r\nAt its heart is the Apiqe unit, a revolutionary technical innovation that reduces the filtration and \r\npurification engine to one simple valve. More about several patents? Purifier.   \r\n\r\nApiqe’s breakthrough technology is contained in one sleek unit — not just for aesthetics — but to \r\nminimize the carbon footprint. Connected simply to the mains, Apiqe is noiseless, saves space, \r\ntime and money. It looks cool. It tastes even better.\r\n\r\nApiqe leaves behind contaminants and microorganisms. Leaving you with crisp water containing only \r\nthe salts and minerals nature intended it to have — for drinking or cooking. \r\n\r\nAlways according to your preference. \r\nRoom temperature. Chilled, Hot, and Custom Carbonated to your desire.\r\n\r\n<h6>See our systems!</h6>', 'My Water', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '222-revision-6', '', '', '2011-05-25 14:23:58', '2011-05-25 14:23:58', '', 222, 'http://apiqe.com/2011/05/25/222-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(229, 1, '2011-05-25 14:23:00', '2011-05-25 14:23:00', '<h1>revolutionary technology</h1>\r\n<img src="http://apiqe.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/doted-lines-short.png"/>\r\n\r\nWater is natural. Bottled water isn’t. But natural water can be tainted.\r\n\r\nIn the third world, contaminated water is one of the biggest factors in infant mortality. A child dies every 30 seconds as a result. Even in the U.S., major cities have water supplies that contain lead, chemicals and other impurities.\r\n\r\nBetween Hawaii and California lies a toxic island twice the size of Texas, made from discarded, disposable plastic bottles. Americans discard 60 million plastic bottles each day. Bottled water also harms the Earth. It wastes fossil fuels and water in production and transport. Not to mention, bottles become a major source of waste.\r\n\r\nWhat, then, is the solution? Bottled water?\r\n\r\nFact is, both regulation and enforcement of bottled water safety is weaker than that of tap water. Federal, state, and local environmental agencies require rigorous testing of tap water safety. For that reason, tap water is the very foundation of Apiqe water.\r\n\r\n<h5>FEWER BOTTLES , LESS WASTE</h5>\r\n\r\n•  According to the US Recycling Institute, more than 80% of bottles in the U.S. do not get recycled and end up in landfills\r\n\r\n•  By eliminating the transport of bottled water from manufacturers to distributors to restaurants, offices and homes, pollution and energy consumption are greatly reduced\r\n\r\n•  Apiqe has the lightest carbon footprint in the industry', 'My Water', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '222-revision-5', '', '', '2011-05-25 14:23:00', '2011-05-25 14:23:00', '', 222, 'http://apiqe.com/2011/05/25/222-revision-5/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
